'''Martin McNiff''' (born 23 August 1991) is a Scottish [[association football|footballer]] who plays for  [[Clyde F.C.|Clyde]] as a [[midfielder|Defender]]. McNiff previously played for [[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]], and had two separate loan spells with [[Annan Athletic F.C.|Annan Athletic]] before signing permanently.<ref>{{soccerbase|49940}}</ref>

McNiff became the first Clyde defender to score ten goals in one season since [[1934–35 in Scottish football|1934–35]] in April 2019 and the first defender to register ten goals from open play.<ref>{{cite web|title=McNiff Makes Clyde History|url=https://www.clydefc.co.uk/news/2019/04/03/6059/#.XKf73JhKjIU|publisher=[[Clyde F.C.|Clyde FC]]|accessdate=6 April 2019|date=3 April 2019}}</ref>

